data.title: Paul Mbiybe Verdzekov
data.text:
Paul Mbiybe Verdzekov (22 January 1931 – 26 January 2010) was a Cameroonian prelate of the Catholic Church who served as the archbishop of the Archdiocese of Bamenda

Quotes

[edit]

The names and titles we bear here on earth we must bear lightly indeed, like the numbers jockeys bear on their backs when they ride in a race and which they must set aside when they go home at the end of the race. Our real names and our real titles await us.

Archbishop Paul Verdzekov’s reflection on the 20th anniversary of Fonlon’s passing. (26 August 2006) Beads of Memory
